            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Sacred to the divine Drusilla. Caius Rubellius Blandus, son of Caius, quaestor of the divine Augustus, tribune of the plebs, praetor, consul, proconsul and pontifex.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>This dedication to the divine Drusilla was made by a senator, Caius Rubellius Blandus, who was also responsible for dedications in Lepcis Magna (RIT 269, 330, 331). As Várhelyi (2010, 113) has noted, dedications by senators to divinized members of the domus Augusta are relatively rare.</p> <!-- Add hyperlinks to these inscriptions? -->
            </div>
